INSERT INTO festivals_festival VALUES(131,'Spoffin Off','Netherlands','Amersfoort','CIRCUS','in@spoffin.nl','','2025-08-30','2025-08-30',0,'','late August','A smaller, one-day event called Spoffin Spin-Off featuring approximately thirteen street theatre acts, primarily from the Netherlands, held at various locations in and around the city center of Amersfoort. The event is freely accessible, with visitors having the option to decide what they pay after each show, and all proceeds going directly to the artists. The event concludes with a fire performance.','','','UNKNOWN','');
INSERT INTO festivals_festival VALUES(132,'Festival D''Aurrilac','France','Aurillac','STREET','eclat@aurillac.net','','2025-08-20','2025-08-23',0,'','mid August','The Festival d''Aurillac, also known as the International Street Theatre Festival, will hold its 38th edition in 2025. The festival will spotlight Brazilian creation as part of the ''Saison du Brésil en France,'' featuring around 19 official companies and over 650 independent visiting companies. It draws more than 130,000 attendees over its four days.','','','EMAIL','http://www.aurillac.net/index.php/en/');
INSERT INTO festivals_festival VALUES(133,'Festival Avignon','France','Avignon','THEATRE','festival@festival-avignon.com','','2025-07-05','2025-07-26',0,'','early to late July','The Festival d''Avignon 2025, including both the ''In'' and ''Off'' festivals, transforms Avignon into a global hub for contemporary performing arts. The 79th edition features theatre, dance, music, and multidisciplinary works across various iconic venues. Arabic is the guest language, and choreographer Marlene Monteiro Freitas will open the festival.','','','EMAIL','https://festival-avignon.com/en/professional-15932#section-34136');
INSERT INTO festivals_festival VALUES(134,'Young Stage','Switzerland','Basel','CIRCUS','nadja.hauser@young-stage.com','Nadja Hauser-Berger','2025-09-18','2025-09-22',0,'','mid September','The ''Grande Finale'' of the international circus festival Young Stage Basel, celebrating nearly 20 years of the festival''s history. It showcases young, modern circus artistry with top-class acts from twelve countries, selected from 640 applications across 66 nations. The event includes main shows, workshops, and panel discussions, serving as a significant platform for young circus artists to launch their careers.','','','INVITATION_ONLY','https://www.young-stage.com/en/');
